Reasoning: 
- cs.SD (Sound): The paper proposes a text-to-speech (TTS) model, which is related to sound processing. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The TTS model is based on a sequence-to-sequence neural network, which is a common technique in natural language processing. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The model is formulated as a conditional generative model based on the variational autoencoder (VAE) framework, which is a machine learning technique. 
- cs.SD (Signal Processing): The paper deals with controlling latent attributes in speech synthesis, which involves signal processing techniques. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a novel approach for controllable speech synthesis, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence.
